132nd MAINE LEGISLATURE
FIRST SPECIAL SESSION-2025
Legislative Document No. 1833
S.P. 715 In Senate, April 30, 2025
An Act to Expand Law Education and Training by Creating a Night
Law School Program
Reference to the Committee on Education and Cultural Affairs suggested and ordered
printed.
DAREK M. GRANT
Secretary of the Senate
Presented by Senator BALDACCI of Penobscot.
Cosponsored by Senators: BAILEY of York, RAFFERTY of York.
Printed on recycled paper

1 Be it enacted by the People of the State of Maine as follows:
2 Sec. 1. University of Maine System and University of Maine School of Law
3 to establish night school law program in Orono. By the beginning of the 2028-2029
4 academic year, the University of Maine System in collaboration with the University of
5 Maine School of Law shall establish at the University of Maine at Orono a juris doctor
6 program that allows a student enrolled in the program to fulfill the degree requirements for
7 a juris doctor primarily by attending classes at night through online course work with
8 periodic in-person instruction. By November 4, 2026, the University of Maine System
9 shall submit a report related to the establishment of the night school law program to the
10 Joint Standing Committee on Education and Cultural Affairs.
11 SUMMARY
1122 This bill requires the University of Maine System in collaboration with the University
1133 of Maine School of Law to establish at the University of Maine at Orono a juris doctor
1144 program that allows a student enrolled in the program to fulfill the degree requirements for
1155 a juris doctor primarily by attending classes at night through online course work with
1166 periodic in-person instruction. By November 4, 2026, the University of Maine System
1177 must submit a report related to the establishment of the program to the Joint Standing
1188 Committee on Education and Cultural Affairs.
